<item>
            <title>[WFLY-6200] connection-url is required even when not used</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-6200</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Per the comments on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-6157&quot; title=&quot;Connection URL ignored for SQL Server datasource&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFLY-6157&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFLY-6157&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-6198&quot; title=&quot;When a datasource has no connection-properties and its driver has defined datasource-class a warning should be issued&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFLY-6198&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFLY-6198&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, connection-url is ignored in a datasource if datasource-class is defined. However, connection-url is currently mandatory. If it is not present, WildFly fails to start:&lt;/p&gt;
